docs.lead_paragraph: Some doctors at New York City’s biggest private hospital system appear to no longer accept certain plans, forcing some patients to change doctors.

headline.main: Patients Fear Mt. Sinai Will Drop Low-Cost Insurance Plans
headline.print_headline: Patients Fear Mount Sinai Will Drop Low-Cost Insurance Plans

docs.abstract: Some doctors in the Mount Sinai Health System, New York City's biggest private hospital system, are no longer accepting certain low-cost insurance plans, which is preventing a number of patients from seeing their longtime doctors; it is unclear whether changes are limited to a few doctors or part of a movement by institution to squeeze out low-paying plans under health care reform law or force higher reimbursement rates.

docs.lead_paragraph: Hildreth Meière is not exactly a household name, but her Art Deco mosaics and murals live on landmarks in New York.

headline.seo: Hildreth Meière, the Forgotten Art Deco Artist
headline.main: If These Walls Could Speak, They’d Say Her Name
headline.print_headline: If These Walls Could Speak, They’d Say Her Name

docs.abstract: Hildreth Meiere, most prominent muralist of the 1920s, radically advanced her field and helped introduce America to the modernism of Art Deco; Meiere's work went largely unrecognized for decades, but her mosaics and murals live on at several prominent landmarks in New York City.
